THE ST. LOUIS. Petition of PENNSYLVANIA R. CO. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. October 21, 1929. No. 10. Bigham, Englar, Jones & Houston, of New York City (Charles W. Hagen, of New York City, of counsel), for appellants. Burlingham, Veeder, Fearey, Clark & Hupper, of New York City (Chauncey I. Clark and Frederic Conger, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree [35 F.(2d) 741] affirmed.
